The flavor combination is nice, but I felt this recipe wasn't really worth the effort -- especially the large pile of dishes afterwards.

Rating: 3
This was a nice change to add some flavor to turkey. I will definitly make this again.

Rating: 3
Didn't have turkey so used chicken tenderloins instead: two tenderloins on either side of 1-2 thin thin slices of prosciutto. I used fairly coarse whole wheat (not Panko) bread crumbs. Some eaters including two teenagers were suspicious of the caper sauce, but it really MADE the dish. Will definitely be making again.

Rating: 3
What a geat way to use turkey! This is an easy, tasty week night dinner. I served it with pasta and a light tomato sauce, salad, and crusty bread. Be sure to use Panko crumbs.